<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,366,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
The genus is known from all biogeographical regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[782,937,366,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1994) Scuttle flies: the Phoridae. Chapman &amp; Hall, London, xii + 467 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 011 - 1288 - 8" type="book" year="1994">
Disney, 
<number box="[877,937,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), although it is not particularly speciose. In 
<collectingCountry box="[151,216,402,427]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Israel</collectingCountry>
, it has already been represented by cosmopolitan 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz, 1925" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1925" box="[803,1093,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Conicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[803,917,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">C. tibialis</emphasis>
Schmitz, 
<number box="[1037,1093,402,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Disney" box="[1112,1431,402,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Nussbaum, Y. (1990) Phoridae (Diptera) from Israel. Israel Journal of Entomology, 24, 107 - 114." type="journal article" year="1990">
Disney &amp; Nussbaum, 
<number box="[1372,1431,403,427]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lengyel" box="[151,329,438,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" refString="Lengyel, G. D. (2011 a) The first Rhynchomicropteron Annandale, 1912 (Diptera, Phoridae) species from the Palearctic region, with taxonomic and faunistic notes on the fauna of Israel. Zootaxa, 2885, 23 - 32." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="a">
Lengyel, 
<number box="[257,316,439,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). Two species below are new records for the country.
</paragraph>
